TITLE: Kansas splash pad linked to dozens of gastrointestinal illnesses, CDC says
SUMMARY: Health officials said dozens of people who visited Tanganyika Wildlife Park in Goddard, Kansas, last year suffered gastrointestinal illnesses linked to the park's splash pad.

TITLE: Retiring Golf analyst Nick Faldo breaks down in tears after 16 years on air: 'I'm ready'
SUMMARY: English golfing legend Nick Faldo retired on Sunday from the CBS commentary booth after the final hole of the 2022 Wyndham Championship.

TITLE: New Jersey man who was sentenced to six decades in prison will have new trial following appeal
SUMMARY: An NJ man who was convicted of stabbing his girlfriend to death in 2011 is having a new trial after appealing the ruling. Jurors convicted him after just 45 minutes in his last trial.

TITLE: Cardinals sweep Yankees behind home runs from Nolan Arenado, Paul DeJong
SUMMARY: The Cardinals beat the Yankees in a game that went almost four and half hours. Frankie Montas got hit hard in his first start as a Yankee, giving up a home run to Nolan Arenado.

TITLE: Delaware Memorial Bridge construction expected to cause delays
SUMMARY: Traffic delays are expected due to construction of the Delaware memorial Bridge. Two lanes of the Delaware side of the bridge will be closed to traffic in the first phase.

TITLE: Oregon woman demands action from Portland officials after being shot in the face while driving
SUMMARY: Oregon's Katie Guzenko joined "Fox & Friends" to call for action from Portland's city council on gun violence after she was shot in the face while driving.

TITLE: Jesse Winker's grand slam helps Mariners to victory over Angels
SUMMARY: The Mariners beat the Angels behind Jesse Winker's grand slam as the Angels continue to struggle. Marco Gonzales struck out seven in the victory for the Mariners.

TITLE: Australia cricket star Tahlia McGrath plays in match despite testing positive for COVID-19
SUMMARY: Australian cricket star batter Tahlia McGrath tested positive for COVID-19 before the gold medal match against India but still played in the match as England's protocols allowed it.

TITLE: Brighton hands Manchester United, new manager Erik ten Hag first loss
SUMMARY: Brighton jumped out to an early lead and held on to it for the rest of the game as Manchester United never got anything going until the second half when Cristiano Ronaldo entered.

TITLE: 9-year-old Baltimore boy allegedly kills 15-year-old girl in shooting, police say
SUMMARY: 15-year-old Nykayia Strawder was shot and killed in Baltimore after a 9-year-old boy fired a gun at her head Saturday. Relatives say the boy had fought with her brother.
